libtool: remove OpenBSD specific performance hack for ranlib

The -t flag was used as a performance hack for ranlib. The flag was
supported by the GNU toolchain, but is an invalid option that causes
a fatal error with the LLVM toolchain.

Related upstream changes:
- https://cgit.git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/libtool.git/commit/?id=1ae386ba78f499d366c3123d0737745589c5dfec
- https://cgit.git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/libtool.git/commit/?id=5a7193dbfb8c90e1b1306a360a1b0c80ef8c4de0


--- a/configure
+++ b/configure
@@ -7677,7 +7677,7 @@
 
 if test -n "$RANLIB"; then
   case $host_os in
-  bitrig* | openbsd*)
+  bitrig*)
     old_postinstall_cmds="$old_postinstall_cmds~\$RANLIB -t \$tool_oldlib"
     ;;
   *)
